My project, DFAME is looking for people to participate in user interviews. Please consider picking a time: <https://calendly.com/dfame/dfame-onborading>

DFAME enables creators, brands, artists, or influencers to turn their community into an economy. Users join in by owning the community tokens which grants them rights to media content as well as the ability to collaborate within the community. The creator's community becomes its own network and tokens represent new value creation distributed amongst all members.

Hey all, *Opportunity Alert:*

*CryptoChicks Hatchery online program* is *welcoming new female founders to incubate their blockchain startups with a help of business building curriculum and mentorship help of successful blockchain entrepreneurs*. Please see the information deck <https://bit.ly/CCHatcheryFounder2020> and website <https://cryptochickshatchery.com> for more information.

*My experience*
I attended the program last year with its first cohort with a different project. The commitment is low-key - you choose your schedule to speak to the mentors and you present about your progress during the scheduled meeting times (once a quarter). The program also started to get funding as well and we had an opportunity to onboard a summer intern that they would pay a stipend for but we didn’t pursue it. Overall, a good addition to an accelerator or if you are looking for more marketing and to make more connections but don’t expect lots of funding or an intensive program.

*FUN FACT*: CryptoChicks was founded by Vitalik’s mom to help more women get into blockchain.
